# === Godot 4 Project Rules ===

## Language
- Use GDScript (Godot 4 syntax)
- Prefer strongly typed variables

## Architecture
- Use Node-based architecture
- Avoid monolithic scripts
- Split logic into components:
  - SkillComponent
  - HitboxComponent
  - StateMachine

## Naming
- Classes: PascalCase
- Variables: snake_case
- Signals: snake_case

## Scene Rules
- One responsibility per scene
- Do NOT create deep node trees
- Keep scenes reusable

## Performance
- Avoid spawning nodes every frame
- Reuse objects (object pooling if needed)
- Prefer data-driven systems

## Animation
- Do NOT rely heavily on AnimationPlayer
- Prefer frame-based animation systems

## Combat System
- Use hitbox / hurtbox system
- Avoid physics-based damage detection
- All attacks must be event-driven

## Skills
- Skills must be data-driven (Resource)
- Avoid hardcoding skill logic
- Use time-based or frame-based events

## Code Style
- Avoid magic numbers
- Use constants
- Keep functions small (<50 lines)

## Testing
- Prefer deterministic logic
- Allow AI/TestAgent to trigger actions

## Forbidden
- No tightly coupled systems
- No direct node path dependencies (use signals)
- No logic inside UI nodes

## Combat Rules (DNF-style)

- Combat must be frame-based, not animation-driven
- Hitbox must be controlled by frame events
- Each frame can define:
  - hitbox
  - movement
  - effects

- No direct damage in animation
- All damage goes through Hitbox system

## Skill System

- Skill = Animation + Events + Data
- Use SkillData (Resource)
- Support multi-hit attacks
- Support cancel windows

## AI Testing

- All skills must be callable by AI
- No input-only logic